/A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 6:28:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Paladins are the masters of spell interrupts (potentially) amongst the melee classes, so I'd prefer AA points being used to increase likelihood of a spell interrupt from a bash and possibly a faster reset time (AA = more arm strength and faster recovery).<br>
<br>
I would also like to see AA points tied to another shield characteristic - deflection (highly polished shield?).  Spell has chance to be resisted and deflected onto an enemy mob, perhaps 5% at AA1, 10% at AA2 and 15% or 20% at AA3.<br>
<br>
Fun to play around with the idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 7:03:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> I think the use of a shield should be highly valuable before your even able to make AA exp. I think the clearest cut method of providing that is a block skill, similar to dodge and parry but requires a shield to be equipped. This is afterall the reason shield were invented, to block blows. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> 
<br>58 Knight of Brell
<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker
</bold>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udrachan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drachan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 7:50:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> The idea is nice Varner, in essence that would be the same effect as parry or dodge, i. e. avoid a blow.<br>
<br>
So rather than have to work up yet another skill remove the parry cap with shield for paladins. I could envision parry skill with shield (what you call block) up to 255, like the defense skill.<br>
<br>
And add an AA to increase this block skill probability with shield.<br>
<br>
That would work in the sense of the paladin's defensive paradigm and work in the sense of giving back value to shields.<br>
