<br>
I'm all for getting some nice effects or significantly increased stats on shields though.  Right now using a shield is more of an afterthought for many of us, only when we have obtained a nice 1H weapon like the DMF or Massive Dragonclaw Shard.  I'd like the shields themselves to be the reason we consider using them, not just because we have that secondary slot free. <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 8:39:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> An interesting concept might be the ability to hide behind a shield during a dragons breath, reducing the damage significantly. That would make shields a very viable option for dragon/tov raids. <br>
<br>
It could similar act on meele damage. While using the &quot;guard&quot; skill meele damage taken from a mob would be reduced but all casting/meele from a player would be paused during that also.<br>
<br>
So when a shield wearing player gets unwanted aggro, they could raise the shield and guard themselves. Possible give an NPC a chance to knock the shield out of guard position for increase damage taken.<br>
<br>
